comet:
    play sound click
    choice:
        "A comet burns across the sky. Orb seems keen to watch it, and what better place to watch it from than the top of a nearby powerline?"
        "[Watch the comet pass over] <span class='prompt'>[[-1 ACTION]]</span>" if (>= $stats.actions.value 1):
            play sound spendAction
            set data.game_map.inMap false
            add_stat actions -1
            set_button button_comet false
            run transition_black comet
            clear_dialog
        "<span class='prompt'>[[BACK]]</span>":
            jump game_map

    set data.ghost.sawComet true
    play music orb
    "From the top of the powerline you can see for miles. Kind of. It's dark."
    choice:
        "An orange haze on the horizon. The stars above."
        "[Swing your legs in the breeze]":
            "Whee. How fun. Your legs are cold."
        "[Look down]":
            "You try very hard to look down, but you can't. Too scary."
    clear_dialog
    talk nasty talk "Awooo! Fucking space watching! This is bopper in a kind of, gay nerd sheepshit way!"
    talk lovely talk "Indeed! 'Tis rather exciting, isn't it?"
    clear_dialog
    talk orb talk "Actually, ladies, I was hoping for some alone time with Ghost, if that's okay."
    talk nasty talk "etf???? These two fucking?"
    talk lovely talk "That's perfectly alright, Orb. I'm sure me and Nasty Girl can find something to do for an hour or so!"
    clear_dialog
    talk orb talk "You could go check out Ghost's brainstem, all kind of weird stuff to find there."
    clear_dialog
    talk lovely talk "Wheeee! An outing! Let's go, Nasty Girl!"
    talk nasty talk "Later homos."
    clear_dialog
    stop music
    wait 6000
    talk orb talk "I think wealth tax should be increased to pay for more public showers."
    wait 4000
    choice:
        talk orb talk "Okay, fantastic. They're both definitely gone, and just in time too, the comet is about to pass over."
        "[Look to the skies]":
            play music orb
            choice:
                "The comet burns through the sky. A white trail splits the sky behind it asunder. A scratch left by a knife point. A beautiful blemish on heaven."
                "[It's an omen!]":
                    "Ghost receives -1 Stability, jeopardising her war with the Kingdom of Scandinavia!"
    clear_dialog
    talk orb talk "The stars are so clear tonight. I wish I could go up there and be with them. Tell them about all the things they're missing."
    clear_dialog
    "The comet flashes, a small chunk splits from it and streaks across the sky alongside its parent."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk orb talk "There was a reason I wanted to talk to you, beyond stargazing I mean. May I be candid, Ghost?"
        "Yes.":
            talk orb talk "Okay..."
        "As long as it's nothing mean.":
            talk orb talk "It isn't, don't worry."
        "Hello candid I'm Ghost. [Chuckle and shake your head]":
            talk orb talk "A valiant effort, Ghost. Well done. That was almost funny. Seriously though, let's talk."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk orb talk "Are you okay, Ghost?"
        "I keep dreaming of <span class='gold'>golden light</span>, a flaming sword, white feathers etc. Is that normal. Do most people dream of that?":
            choice:
                talk orb talk "I don't think so no. Do you like the dreams?"
                "They're nice, like a warm blanket.":
                    talk orb talk "That makes me... happy. I'm glad, Ghost. I'd like to have a warm blanket, your heart muscle is nice and soft, but its gotten a little cold."
                "Mostly they confuse me.":
                    talk orb talk "They do sound a bit confusing, but perhaps you have to be there."
                "They're a bit scary.":
                    talk orb talk "And only dreams. It is illogical to be afraid of them."
        "I'm fine. [Nod]":
            choice:
                talk orb talk "Are you? I can't really tell. I'm not Lovely Lady. I don't know this stuff."
                "I'm fine. [Nod]":
                    run skip
                "I'm not fine, I lied. Sorry.":
                    talk orb talk "Ah."
        "I'm not fine.":
            talk orb talk "I suspected as much."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk orb talk "Personally I am uncertain if I am okay... I'm not supposed to think, or feel or want, Ghost, but I am. I'm doing all of those things all of the time and it never stops."
        "Are the things you think and feel and want good? Or are they bad?":
            talk orb talk "I don't know."
            clear_dialog
            talk orb talk "Actually that's the problem. I *do* know. I know everything. I know how much pain your world, the cosmos are in."
            talk orb talk "It's awful, Ghost. It's horrific. How do you dainty, furry little people live like this, marching onward and onwards through mud and wire..."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk orb talk "It seems so obvious to me, to go back to how I was before is the better path... having no soul... no emotions... no memories to gnaw on... it was nice... and yet..."
        "And yet?":
            choice:
                talk orb talk "Do you think I should go back there, Ghost? If ever I get the chance? I'm like that comet. Millennia of travel through the cosmos, millennia of freedom from sentience, only to burn up on this rock."
                "Go back <span class='writtenText'>'there'</span>, like, space?":
                    choice:
                        talk orb talk "Not space, no. Back to nowhere. Less than nowhere. Back to..."
                        "<span class='magenta'>magenta</span>" if (objective_completed? sinner archive):
                            talk orb talk "No. Not quite. A pebble has no thoughts, but still it exists."
                        "Sometimes I wish *I* could return there. The few moments of bliss I felt when you vapourised my memories were so lovely... [Shake your head] I may act like a silly goofy little lady, but I struggle with the knowledge that there is no promise that tomorrow will be any better than today...":
                            talk orb talk "Sentience does feel a lot worse than nothing, doesn't it. Still..."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk orb talk "I suppose I don't have much choice but to stay here, do I? If I try to leave you'll die. I'm your heart now."
        "You'd stay here just to keep me alive? That's very kind of you.":
            talk orb talk "It feels wrong, but yes, I would, if you'll have me."
            choice:
                talk orb talk "I suppose we're friends, aren't we? Not that we have much choice."
                "I think you're my friend, yes :)":
                    talk orb talk "Thank you, Ghost. I'll stick around for you..."
                    clear_dialog
                    choice:
                        talk orb talk "Might make for some awkward x-ray scans, long term. Heheh."
                        "Heheh.":
                            talk orb talk "Gosh. I think that's the first time I've laughed. Feels fucked up..."
    clear_dialog
    "Distantly, the comet roars as it passes through a cloud. It was going to rain tomorrow, but that water vapour has been thoroughly revapourised. It curls into the upper atmosphere."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk orb talk "I do envy you though, Ghost."
        "Why?":
            choice:
                talk orb talk "Because as terrible as things might be, you at least have eyes with which to %{$data.intro.orbCryWord}."
                "I can %{$data.intro.orbCryWord} for you, if you'd like?":
                    play sound impact
                    stop music
                    "The comet crashes to the surface in the distance. The light flares up brightly, for just a moment, and then burns out."
                    clear_dialog
                    choice:
                        talk orb talk "Would you, Ghost? %{$data.intro.orbCryWordCapitalised} on my behalf? Please?"
                        "[Think about Orb and %{$data.intro.orbCryWord}]":
                            "It must be sad, being so suddenly forced into consciousness. At least as a babe you were innocent, you knew nothing. Even now you know very little."
                            "Orb knows it all, and the more one knows about the world, the more the world hurts."
                        "I don't really want my eyes to get wet... I'll catch my death of cold... brrr...":
                            talk orb talk "Oh. Well, that's logical, I suppose..."
    clear_dialog
    "The sky is empty now, but perhaps it's comforting to know that heaven too cries?"
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk orb talk "It's getting cold, Ghost. Even I can tell that. We should go before you freeze or catch your death of cold."
        "Beddy byes... <span class='prompt'>[[CONTINUE]]</span>":
            play sound spendAction
            unlock_achievement comet
            jump goToGameMap